Use `dotnet test --hotreload` to watch for changes and re-run tests automatically:

```bash
dotnet test --hotreload
```

Since your `global.json` already sets `"runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform"` (MSTest 3.8+), hot reload is supported out of the box. It will watch for file saves and re-run affected tests.

---

**About the failing test:** `RemoveStock` doesn't throw when the quantity exceeds stock — it just goes negative. You'll need to add a guard in `RemoveStock`, e.g.:

```csharp
public void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)
{
    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);
    if (quantity > current)
        throw new InvalidOperationException("Insufficient stock");
    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;
}
```

With hot reload running, just save the file and the test will re-run automatically.
